The paper deals with language modeling using deep neural networks, specifically for named entity recognition in Historic German. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also discusses pre-trained language models, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning), as well as deep neural networks, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with low-resource datasets, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and character-based models, which falls under cs.DL (Deep Learning).
